Basic input/output

Using \n is better than std::endl
  coz, a \n is a simple escape sequence that adds a newline charachter which is low-level operation
  Whereas, the std::endl adds a newline charachter as well as it flushes the output buffer
  Flushing buffer is considered a more costly operation in terms of performance when we are printing a large amount of data

using namespace std
  we are telling the compiler that we are using all the names in the std namespace withoout explicitly mentioning std::
